description: From a- +‎ gee. A preposition of state + gee (“to move to one side”), from gee or jee, a call to a horse to move to one side.

adverbs.description: agee (comparative more agee, superlative most agee)

entries.meaning: (Scotland, dialect, archaic) Aside, on or to one side; awry; off from the straight line.
